    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Parse documents with Google Drive and PostgreSQL in real time\n\n**Pattern:** File Processing · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nParse documents with Google Drive and PostgreSQL in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual ocr & extraction is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Export All Rows (PostgreSQL) → Serialize to CSV → Upload Backup to Google Drive → Backup Size Sane? → Sort Documents Newest First → Align Field Names\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to file processing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating ocr & extraction in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Postgres connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "3ee20a79-fe8c-c670-9b0d-3960f9d59e39",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your ocr & extraction process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
